               <head>Durr-e Maknun of ‘Abd al-Fattah</head>
               <msContents>
                  <summary>1 copy of Durr-i maknūn by ʿAbd al-Fattāḥ al-Ḥusaynī al-ʿAskarī</summary>
                  <msItem class="http://lccn.loc.gov/sh2008112367 http://lccn.loc.gov/sh2006003807" n="1" xml:id="Uk_Delhi_Persian_1000-item1">
                     <author>
                        <persName xml:lang="per-Latn-x-lc" type="supplied" key="person_f4666">ʿAbd al-Fattāḥ al-Ḥusaynī al-ʿAskarī</persName>
                        <persName xml:lang="per" type="supplied" key="person_f4666">عبد الفتّاح الحسينى العسكرى </persName>
                     </author>
                     <title xml:lang="per-Latn-x-lc" key="work_7413">Durr-i maknūn</title>
                     <title xml:lang="per" key="work_7413">درّ مكنون</title>
                     <note>
                        <p>Epitome and commentary on Rumi’s <title>Mas̲navī-'i maʿnavī</title> by the author <persName key="person_f4666" role="aut">ʿAbd al-Fattāḥ al-Ḥusaynī al-ʿAskarī</persName>. 

                        </p>
                        <p>The work is dedicated to the Timurid or Mughal <persName key="person_6178410" role="oth">Emperor ʿĀlamgīr I</persName>. 

                        </p>
                        <p>Not dated at end. 
</p>
                        <p>Many detailed annotations in margins. 
</p>
                        <p>Illuminate ʿunvān in the sixteenth-century Timurid style cut and pasted from an older source; black and yellow rulings. 
</p>
                        <p>Distinct shikastah āmīz, with verses in two columns, on purplish pink paper. 
</p>
                        <p>Pencil foliation. 
</p>
                        <p>Only front flap from soft leather binding survives (brown leather exterior, deep pink leather doublure). 
</p>
                        <p>Condition fragile. 
</p>
                     </note>
                     <textLang mainLang="per" otherLangs="ara">Persian and Arabic</textLang>
                     <note>
